Interface Call

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ListenerTarget<CallListener>

    public interface Call
extends ListenerTarget<CallListener>
    An object that represents a voice and/or video call.

      • answer

        void answer(MediaDirection audioDirection,
            MediaDirection videoDirection)
        Answer an incoming call.

        Note that the SDK only supports one call at a time. If you answer an incoming call whilst another is in progress, then that other call will be terminated.

        Parameters:
        audioDirection - Required audio direction.
        videoDirection - Required video direction.

      • answer

        void answer(boolean audio,
            boolean video)
        Deprecated. Use MediaDirection parameters instead of booleans.
        Answers an incoming call.

        Note that the SDK only supports one call at a time. If you answer an incoming call whilst another is in progress, then that other call will be terminated.

        Parameters:
        audio - Whether to use audio.
        video - Whether to use video.
